org.telegram.abilitybots.api.objects

Class EndUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.telegram.abilitybots.api.objects.EndUser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class EndUser
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class serves the purpose of separating the basic Telegram User and the augmented EndUser.

    It adds proper hashCode, equals, toString as well as useful utility methods such as shortName() and fullName().

        public java.lang.String fullName()
        The full name is identified as the concatenation of the first and last name, separated by a space. This method can return an empty name if both first and last name are empty.
        Returns:
        the full name of the user

      • shortName

        public java.lang.String shortName()
        The short name is one of the following:
        1. First name
        2. Last name
        3. Username
        The method will try to return the first valid name in the specified order.
        Returns:
        the short name of the user
